#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:1 of
msgid "Draw samples from a Gumbel distribution."
msgstr "从 Gumbel 分布中抽取样本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:3 of
msgid ""
"Draw samples from a Gumbel distribution with specified location and "
"scale.  For more information on the Gumbel distribution, see Notes and "
"References below."
msgstr ""
"从具有指定位置和尺度参数的 Gumbel 分布中抽取样本。有关 Gumbel 分布的更多"
"信息，请参见下面的说明和参考文献。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:7 of
msgid "The location of the mode of the distribution. Default is 0."
msgstr "分布众数的位置。默认值为 0。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:9 of
msgid "The scale parameter of the distribution. Default is 1."
msgstr "分布的尺度参数。默认值为 1。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:11 of
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n *"
" k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is"
" returned if ``loc`` and ``scale`` are both scalars. Otherwise, "
"``np.broadcast(loc, scale).size`` samples are drawn."
msgstr ""
"输出形状。如果给定形状，例如 ``(m, n, k)``，则抽取 ``m * n * k`` 个样本。"
"如果 size 为 ``None``（默认），并且 ``loc`` 和 ``scale`` 都是标量，则返回"
"单个值。否则抽取 ``np.broadcast(loc, scale).size`` 个样本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:16 of
msgid "Desired chunk size on each dimension"
msgstr "每一维度上期望的分块大小"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:18 of
msgid "Allocate the tensor on GPU if True, False as default"
msgstr "如果为 True，则在 GPU 上分配张量，默认为 False"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:20 of
msgid "Data-type of the returned tensor."
msgstr "返回张量的数据类型。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:23 of
msgid "**out** -- Drawn samples from the parameterized Gumbel distribution."
msgstr "**out** -- 从参数化的 Gumbel 分布中抽取的样本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:26 of
msgid ""
":py:obj:`scipy.stats.gumbel_l`, :py:obj:`scipy.stats.gumbel_r`, "
":py:obj:`scipy.stats.genextreme`, :py:obj:`weibull`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:29 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:30 of
msgid ""
"The Gumbel (or Smallest Extreme Value (SEV) or the Smallest Extreme Value"
" Type I) distribution is one of a class of Generalized Extreme Value "
"(GEV) distributions used in modeling extreme value problems. The Gumbel "
"is a special case of the Extreme Value Type I distribution for maximums "
"from distributions with \"exponential-like\" tails."
msgstr ""
"Gumbel（或最小极值（SEV）或最小极值 I 型）分布是一类用于建模极值问题的"
"广义极值（GEV）分布之一。Gumbel 是来自具有“指数类”尾部分布的最大值的"
"极值 I 型分布的特殊情况。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:36 of
msgid "The probability density for the Gumbel distribution is"
msgstr "Gumbel 分布的概率密度为"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:38 of
msgid ""
"p(x) = \\frac{e^{-(x - \\mu)/ \\beta}}{\\beta} e^{ -e^{-(x - \\mu)/\n"
"\\beta}},\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:41 of
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mu` is the mode, a location parameter, and :math:`\\beta` "
"is the scale parameter."
msgstr "其中 :math:`\\mu` 是众数，即位置参数，:math:`\\beta` 是尺度参数。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:44 of
msgid ""
"The Gumbel (named for German mathematician Emil Julius Gumbel) was used "
"very early in the hydrology literature, for modeling the occurrence of "
"flood events. It is also used for modeling maximum wind speed and "
"rainfall rates.  It is a \"fat-tailed\" distribution - the probability of"
" an event in the tail of the distribution is larger than if one used a "
"Gaussian, hence the surprisingly frequent occurrence of 100-year floods. "
"Floods were initially modeled as a Gaussian process, which underestimated"
" the frequency of extreme events."
msgstr ""
"Gumbel（以德国数学家 Emil Julius Gumbel 命名）很早就在水文学文献中用于"
"建模洪水事件的发生。它也用于建模最大风速和降雨率。它是一种“厚尾”分布——"
"分布尾部事件的概率比使用高斯分布时更大，因此出现了令人惊讶的频繁的"
"百年一遇洪水。洪水最初被建模为高斯过程，这低估了极端事件的频率。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:53 of
msgid ""
"It is one of a class of extreme value distributions, the Generalized "
"Extreme Value (GEV) distributions, which also includes the Weibull and "
"Frechet."
msgstr ""
"它是一类极值分布，即广义极值（GEV）分布中的一种，还包括 Weibull 和 "
"Frechet。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:57 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The function has a mean of :math:`\\mu + 0.57721\\beta` and a variance of"
" :math:`\\frac{\\pi^2}{6}\\beta^2`."
msgstr ""
"该函数的均值为 :math:`\\mu + 0.57721\\beta`，方差为 :math:`\\frac{\\pi^2}"
"{6}\\beta^2`。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:61 of
msgid "引用"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:62 of
msgid ""
"Gumbel, E. J., \"Statistics of Extremes,\" New York: Columbia University "
"Press, 1958."
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.gumbel.gumbel:64 of
msgid ""
"Reiss, R.-D. and Thomas, M., \"Statistical Analysis of Extreme Values "
"from Insurance, Finance, Hydrology and Other Fields,\" Basel: Birkhauser "
"Verlag, 2001."
msgstr ""

